1.title: Den du nicht siehst

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

1.plot: A woman is found dead after a celebration - as Inspector Robert Anders and team investigates, someone leaks information to a journalist creating a security problem. After a second woman is murdered, it is feared a serial killer is on the loose. In addition, Robert's son, Nicklas, is bullied at school.

2.title: Näher als du denkst

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

2.plot: A young girl is forced off a cliff while riding her bicycle. The girl is later identified as a student/worker at the stable where Robert's daughter, Ida, takes lessons. Once again details are leaked to the press...could it be a police officer? The murder affects things at home, as Robert's relationships with his daughter and father come into play.

3.title: An einem einsamen Ort

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

3.plot: An archeologist is murdered and found in the woods, a victim of a Viking ritual. Was it her father (a property owner who wants to develop a "sacred" site), the protestors (Viking revivalists against the development), her University advisor (whom she may have been filing sexual harassment charges against) or someone else? Niklas is feeling neglected as Emma (a teacher and close friend of the family) has come to stay for awhile with her newborn baby, taking Ida's attention and playtime. Robert also deals with his troubled relationship with his father.

4.title: Sommerzeit

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

4.plot: Flashback 13 years - two teenage sisters celebrating and drinking on the island - one passes out and when she awakes finds her sister missing - who is later found dead. Present time - an explosion at a stone quarry results in a death ... accident or murder? Robert's mother comes for a visit.

5.title: Der sterbende Dandy

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

5.plot: An art dealer is found murdered - the investigation uncovers the theft of major artwork. Motive leads to a betrayed wife, a mistress and a lover. Robert's jealousy is triggered when Line's old boyfriend makes an appearance and an overnight sailing trip ensues.

6.title: Schwarzer Engel

episode of.title: The Inspector and the Sea (TV Series 2007– )

6.plot: A prominent architect is found dead at a celebratory event - Inspector Anders and team's investigation leads through mutiple suspects with complex alibis. At home, Line becomes more discontented and Robert seems oblivious until Line leaves with the kids to visit her friend in Brittany.

imdb.plot outline: German police inspector Robert Anders a family man who lives with his Swedish wife and investigates murder cases located in the spectacular landscapes of Swedish island of Gotland , it is based on the best-selling crime novels by the Swedish author Mari Jungstedt.
